
<div class="container col-xxl-8 px-4 py-5">
    <div class="row flex-lg-row-reverse align-items-center g-5 py-5">
        <div class="col-10 col-sm-8 col-lg-6">
            <img src="~/images/screenshot.png"
                 class="d-block mx-lg-auto img-fluid rounded"
                 alt="Music tool screenshot" width="800" loading="lazy">
            <p class="text-center text-muted small mt-2">
                @Localizer["Tool Interface Preview"]
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6">
            <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold text-body-emphasis lh-1 mb-3">
                @Localizer["'See' the Language of Music"]
            </h1>
            <p class="lead">
                @Localizer["Welcome to the interactive music theory tool. We help you connect the abstract concepts of music theory—the Chromatic Scale, the Circle of Fifths, and the piano keyboard—allowing you to truly 'see' how music works."]
            </p>
            <hr class="my-4">
            <p class="text-muted">
                @Localizer["Whether you are a beginner student, a curious enthusiast, or an experienced producer, this tool will provide an intuitive sandbox for exploring keys, harmony, and scale structures."]
            </p>

            <div class="d-grid gap-3 d-md-flex justify-content-md-start mt-4">
                <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Major"
                   class="btn btn-primary btn-lg px-4 me-md-2 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-sun lucide-sm me-2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="4"></circle><path d="M12 2v2"></path><path d="M12 20v2"></path><path d="m4.93 4.93 1.41 1.41"></path><path d="m17.66 17.66 1.41 1.41"></path><path d="M2 12h2"></path><path d="M20 12h2"></path><path d="m6.34 17.66-1.41 1.41"></path><path d="m19.07 4.93-1.41 1.41"></path></svg>
                    @Localizer["Explore Major"]
                </a>
                <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Minor"
                   class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-lg px-4 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-moon lucide-sm me-2"><path d="M12 3a6 6 0 0 0 9 9 9 9 0 1 1-9-9Z"></path></svg>
                    @Localizer["Explore Minor"]
                </a>
            </div>

            <div class="row g-4 mt-0 mt-lg-4">
                <div class="col-lg-6">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div class="card-header">
                            <h5 class="card-title mb-0">@Localizer["Interactive Piano"]</h5>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <div class="piano-container table-responsive">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col-lg-6">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div class="card-header">
                            <h5 class="card-title mb-0">@Localizer["Key Signature"]</h5>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <div id="key-signature-container"
                                 class="d-flex flex-column flex-md-row justify-content-center align-items-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div id="localization-data" 
data-tonic="@Localizer["Tonic"]"
 style="display: none;"></div>
<hr class="feature-divider">

<div class="container px-4 py-5" id="features">
    <h2 class="pb-2 border-bottom">@Localizer["Why is music designed this way?"]</h2>
    <p class="lead fs-5 mb-4">
        @Localizer["Music isn't magic; it's a brilliant combination of math, physics, and patterns. Our tool reveals these patterns:"]
    </p>

    <div class="row g-4 py-5 row-cols-1 row-cols-lg-3">

        <div class="feature col">
            <div class="feature-icon d-inline-flex align-items-center justify-content-center text-bg-primary bg-gradient fs-2 mb-3 p-3 rounded-3">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-layout-grid" width="40" height="40"><rect width="18" height="18" x="3" y="3" rx="2"></rect><rect width="7" height="7" x="3" y="3"></rect><rect width="7" height="7" x="14" y="3"></rect><rect width="7" height="7" x="14" y="14"></rect><rect width="7" height="7" x="3" y="14"></rect></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">@Localizer["Deconstructing the 12-Tone System"]</h3>
            <p>
                @Localizer["Why is an octave divided into 12 keys? Modern music is built on '12-Tone Equal Temperament,' a brilliant mathematical compromise that allows all keys to sound 'acceptable.' Our Chromatic Circle makes this abstract pitch system visually intuitive."]
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature col">
            <div class="feature-icon d-inline-flex align-items-center justify-content-center text-bg-primary bg-gradient fs-2 mb-3 p-3 rounded-3">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-compass" width="40" height="40"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><polygon points="16.24 7.76 14.12 14.12 7.76 16.24 9.88 9.88 16.24 7.76"></polygon></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">@Localizer["The Magic of the Circle of Fifths"]</h3>
            <p>
                @Localizer["Keys are not isolated. The 'Circle of Fifths' is music's compass, revealing the order of all key signatures (C -> G -> D...) and their harmonic relationships. It's the core blueprint for composition, arrangement, and improvisation."]
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature col">
            <div class="feature-icon d-inline-flex align-items-center justify-content-center text-bg-primary bg-gradient fs-2 mb-3 p-3 rounded-3">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-link-2" width="40" height="40"><path d="M9 17H7A5 5 0 0 1 7 7h2"></path><path d="M15 7h2a5 5 0 0 1 0 10h-2"></path><line x1="8" x2="16" y1="12" y2="12"></line></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">@Localizer["Connecting Everything"]</h3>
            <p>
                @Localizer["Theory can be dry, but watching it in action is fun. The core value of this tool is 'real-time synchronization.' When you select a new key, the Chromatic Circle, Circle of Fifths, piano keys, and staff notation update instantly. You'll immediately understand why G Major has only one sharp!"]
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
